Version 3.1.4
Allow method calls of import (fixes #135) (#150)

Check logical assignment operators (fixes #147) (#149)

Although in theory, assignment to `.innerHTML` where relevant should never have `.innerHTML` as `undefined` or `null`, we should probably err on the side of caution.
Update babel and deal with newer 'import' parsing (#148)

add Typescript support (#137)

* Add support for TSTypeAssertion (no-op)
* Adds support for TSAsExpression - allowed in assignment when the underlying javascript expression is allowed.
* Adds support for the null coalescing operator. We recurse into this node's expression property.
